## 1. Assets and environments\
\
**Code (this repo)**\
\
- Monorepo with:\
  - API: `apps/api` (NestJS, uses Prisma via `@repo/database`)\
  - Web: `apps/web` (Next.js, talks to API via HTTP)\
  - Database layer: `packages/database` (Prisma schema + migrations: `prisma/schema.prisma`)\
\
**Databases**\
\
- Cloud SQL (Postgres):\
  - `nexus-dev-postgres` (dev DB)\
  - `nexusprod-v2` (prod DB)\
- Local Postgres (optional):\
  - Docker Compose in `infra/docker/docker-compose.yml` exposes Postgres on `localhost:5432` with `nexus_user` / `nexus_password` / DB `nexus_db`. This is mostly for fully-local experiments.\
\
**Runtime services**\
\
- **Local API**: `apps/api`, runs on `http://localhost:8000`\
- **Local web**: `apps/web`, runs on `http://localhost:3000`\
- **Cloud Run API**: `nexus-api` service in GCP (Dockerized via the root `Dockerfile`, deployed by `scripts/deploy-api.sh`)\
- **Vercel web**: builds and serves `apps/web` from GitHub\
\
**Key scripts**\
\
- `scripts/dev-api-cloud-db.sh` \'96 run local API pointed at Cloud SQL (via `DATABASE_URL`)\
- `scripts/db-migrate-cloud.sh` \'96 run Prisma migrations against a Cloud SQL instance (dev or prod, depending on `DATABASE_URL`)\
- `scripts/db-migrate-prod.sh` \'96 production-safe `prisma migrate deploy` against prod DB\
- `scripts/deploy-api.sh` \'96 build Docker image via Cloud Build and deploy API to Cloud Run\
