## 2. Local development, but talking to **GCP database**\
\
### 2.1 Start the Cloud SQL proxy\
\
Pick **dev** or **prod**. For everyday work, use **dev**.\
\
**Dev DB (recommended):**\
\
```bash\
cloud-sql-proxy --port=5433 nexus-enterprise-480610:us-central1:nexus-dev-postgres\
```\
**Prod DB (only when you explicitly want prod):**\
\
```bash\
cloud-sql-proxy --port=5433 nexus-enterprise-480610:us-central1:nexusprod-v2\
```\
This makes Cloud SQL available at `127.0.0.1:5433`.\
\
### 2.2 Set `DATABASE_URL` to point at Cloud SQL\
\
In a new shell (same machine):\
\
```bash\
export DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:<DB_PASSWORD>@127.0.0.1:5433/nexus_db"\
```\
- Replace `<DB_PASSWORD>` with the **Cloud SQL** password (dev or prod, matching the instance the proxy is talking to).\
- This is the canonical connection string used by:\
  - Prisma (`packages/database`)\
  - API (`apps/api` \uc0\u8594  `@repo/database`)\
\
You can quickly sanity check with:\
\
```bash\
psql "$DATABASE_URL"\
```\
If it connects, credentials + proxy are good.\
\
### 2.3 Run local API against Cloud SQL\
\
Use the helper script:\
\
```bash\
cd /Users/pg/nexus-enterprise\
bash ./scripts/dev-api-cloud-db.sh\
```\
What this does:\
\
- Requires `DATABASE_URL` to be set (script will error if not).\
- `cd` into `apps/api`\
- Run `npm run dev` (NestJS dev server)\
- Prisma inside the API uses the same `DATABASE_URL` \uc0\u8594  you\'92re now hitting Cloud SQL from local API.\
\
You can verify:\
\
```bash\
curl -i http://localhost:8000/health\
```\
You want `HTTP/1.1 200 OK` and a JSON body with `ok: true`.\
\
### 2.4 Run local web against **local or Cloud Run API**\
\
The web app uses:\
\
```ts path="/Users/pg/nexus-enterprise/apps/web/app/login/page.tsx" start=5 end=5\
const API_BASE = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL || "http://localhost:8000";\
```\
So:\
\
- For **local API** (dev flow above), you can omit the env var; it will default to `http://localhost:8000`.\
- For **remote API on Cloud Run**, set `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` accordingly.\
\
Local web dev:\
\
```bash\
cd /Users/pg/nexus-enterprise/apps/web\
# For local API:\
# export NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL="http://localhost:8000"\
# For Cloud Run API:\
# export NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL="https://<cloud-run-url>"\
npm run dev\
```\
Then open `http://localhost:3000`.\
