## 3. Where all the passwords / secrets live\
\
### DB passwords (Cloud SQL)\
\
- **Not** stored in the repo (correct).\
- You set them as env vars / shell exports:\
  - Local dev + migrations: `export DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:<DEV_OR_PROD_PASSWORD>@127.0.0.1:5433/nexus_db"`\
  - Scripts use that, they do **not** read `.env` for Cloud SQL.\
\
Checklist:\
\
- [ ] Confirm you have the **dev** and **prod** DB passwords stored in a secure manager (1Password, etc.).\
- [ ] Confirm you can `psql "$DATABASE_URL"` to both dev and prod via proxy.\
\
### API in Cloud Run\
\
- `scripts/deploy-api.sh` assumes the Cloud Run service `nexus-api` is **already configured** with `DATABASE_URL` in its env:\
  - That `DATABASE_URL` should point directly to Cloud SQL (typically through a private connection or connector, often using `localhost` or a Cloud SQL connector string).\
- You manage that via the GCP console or `gcloud run services update`.\
\
Checklist:\
\
- [ ] In Cloud Run service `nexus-api`, verify `DATABASE_URL` env var is set and uses the **prod** DB connection string.\
- [ ] Optionally add `REDIS_URL`, `JWT_SECRET`, etc., as needed (not in this conversation, but they\'92ll be similar).\
\
### Web on Vercel\
\
- Needs to know where the API is:\
\
  - `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL="https://<cloud-run-url>"`\
\
- Add this in Vercel dashboard for each environment (Preview / Production).\
\
Checklist:\
\
- [ ] In Vercel \uc0\u8594  your project \u8594  Settings \u8594  Environment Variables:\
  - Set `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` to the **staging Cloud Run URL** for Preview.\
  - Set `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` to the **prod Cloud Run URL** for Production.\
