## 4. Schema / data structure changes (Prisma)\
\
Prisma lives in `packages/database/prisma/schema.prisma` and `prisma/migrations/*`.\
\
### 4.1 Dev: create + apply migration on **dev DB**\
\
1. Ensure proxy is pointed at `nexus-dev-postgres`.\
2. In `packages/database`, set `DATABASE_URL` for **dev DB**:\
\
```bash\
   cd /Users/pg/nexus-enterprise/packages/database\
   export DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:<DEV_PASSWORD>@127.0.0.1:5433/nexus_db"\
```\
3. Edit `prisma/schema.prisma` as needed.\
4. Create + apply migration:\
\
```bash\
   npx prisma migrate dev --name <migration_name> --schema ./prisma/schema.prisma\
```\
5. Verify behavior locally (API + web pointing at dev DB).\
\
### 4.2 Prod: apply migrations safely\
\
Once you\'92re happy with dev:\
\
1. Switch proxy to prod DB:\
\
```bash\
   cloud-sql-proxy --port=5433 nexus-enterprise-480610:us-central1:nexusprod-v2\
```\
2. Run the production migration script:\
\
```bash\
   cd /Users/pg/nexus-enterprise\
   export DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:<PROD_PASSWORD>@127.0.0.1:5433/nexus_db"\
   ./scripts/db-migrate-prod.sh\
```\
That script:\
\
- `cd`s into `packages/database`\
- Runs `npx prisma migrate deploy` (no new migrations created, just applies existing ones)\
\
Checklist:\
\
- [ ] All schema changes committed under `packages/database/prisma/migrations`.\
- [ ] `db-migrate-prod.sh` runs cleanly against prod DB.\
